<% content_for :title, "HTML Demo About" %>

<section class="hero">
  <p class="eyebrow">Rails rendered this page too.</p>
  <h1>About the HTML-first mode</h1>
  <p>
    Use this mode when you want server-rendered navigation, HTML responses, and selective Vue enhancement
    rather than a full client-side application shell.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="content-grid single-column">
  <article class="info-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Why this mode exists</p>
    <h2>Not every Vue app needs to own the whole page</h2>
    <p>
      This pattern is useful for marketing pages, dashboards with a few interactive controls, and internal tools
      where Rails should stay in charge of routes, rendering, and request lifecycles.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Vue component can still talk back to Rails for persistence, but the navigation model stays simple and
      stateless.
    </p>
  </article>
</section>
